HEADWORD: Cyanite
<hw>Cy"a*nite</hw> <pr>(-n?t)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Cyanic</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>A mineral occurring in
thin-bladed crystals and crystalline aggregates, of a sky-blue color. It
is a silicate of aluminium.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>kyanite</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

